	</tr>
	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				From a balance point of vue (no RPing) :<BR>
- Druids need a big heal at 60, because right now, they are of nearly no use in groups for Velious and plannar raids.<BR>
- Shamans don't need that heal because they ARE already of much use in Velious and plannar raids (uber buffs and mega slows).<BR>
- Warriors in general feel cheated because they are now a normal character in groups, but have no special skill in out of groups situations. Nothing to travel faster. Nothing to heal. AND NOTHING TO ESCAPE. Yeah, Paladins can't escape too, but they heal nearly as good as Druids/Shamans, so...<BR>
I don't talk about soloing. I think it's fair that warriors can't solo. But it is not right that they have nothing to spice their punny, crawling, whining life (SoW me! Heal me! Invis me! Drag my corpse! GG me!).<BR>
And BTW, how long the road is for a warrior to be seen as an invaluable member of a group, except when he is twinked (sigh!).<BR>
Even played very well : pulling perfect preys (how hard it is for us, how easy for monks), switch-taunting, watching all the time at group members health to catch when GroupMates are beeing jumped on, ghetto-bashing,<BR>
the others only think you are &quot;doing your job&quot;, not much. Hardly a thanx or a compliment. Never been given coins for saving someone's butt (Yes, I do give money to guys who buff/heal me).<BR>
Now, think of your easier life, all the other classes and know why we don't like being matched in our &quot;strong-&quot; by someone else ().<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Another point is that warriors have no way to escape or flee encounters on their own. Make them entirely dependant on the skills of their groupmates.<BR>
Question : When in a movie or in books are shown  such dumb warriors ?<BR>
Makes me think that the only true warriors that fits the &quot;Vision&quot; are Ogres. (that's why I play one, hehe...)<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
From a RPing point of vue and a side note, I hate that ppl just run solo classes for funding/twinking their other warrior/monk/hybrids alt. That's plain stupid.<BR>
If you want a nice gear, invest in some trade skills (yeah, like me ;) on the char you are planning to play for real, it makes more sense and makes the world more &quot;normal&quot; :<BR>
&quot;How did you get that whole set of crafted gear at your fifth season ?&quot;<BR>
&quot;- Man, I have a very cool friend&quot;.<BR>
OR, even worse : &quot;- Man, I have a 55 druid alt&quot;.<BR>
I would love to see such people in Real Life, generously giving out ferraris to there best buds...
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
