	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				For all those that dont understand why clerics and warriors are upset about this change, let me enlighten you.  I play both.  46th level cleric, 35th level warrior. <BR>
<BR>
For all you druids and shamans, you have never known what its like to run all the way to a dungeon and shout &quot;XXth level cleric LFG&quot;, and get no response.  Its rare, i admit, but it happens.  Know what I can do then?  NOTHING.  Go somewhere else.  Why?  because Im specialized.  WIthout a group, I cant do anything. <BR>
<BR>
With warriors its twice as bad.  What can my warrior do if he cant find a group?  Solo 1 thing and limp out of the dungeon with 1 bub health.  Camp for the night because I cant make it through a green zone without getting killed.<BR>
<BR>
Now I like playing both of my characters because the above case is rare.  But with these changes, there is NO overwhelming reason to take a warrior in your group.  I get a few extra hitpoints that the druid / shaman / bard is going to complain about healing, along with snide comments about &quot;mana sponge&quot; and all that.  Why would they not want an SK (feign pull), pally (heals himself), ranger (snare kite), monk (feign pull + mend) instead as a tank?<BR>
<BR>
I have yet to see a warrior or cleric post that is not upset about this change.  For those that think we're whining, you have never played either class to a significant level.  And never had the sinking realization that you are not going to get in a group, so you are helpless.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
