			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I'm the rare exception it seems, playing only one character. Because of no experience with the game, I started a cleric, and have been having a ball. He just dinged to 23rd lvl, so I havn't exactly had to worry about acquiring space in groups for raids. I do however have a mind to watching for the future, and its looking mighty grim. <BR>
Now, everyone is agreed that as long as Clerics have complete heal, and ressurect, they will be valued members, but darnit, we want more than that. We don't fight, we sit and stare into our books. We don't solo anything that can get us eps. We heal. thats it. Now, I don't mind other classes having slight healing spells, something to keep others alive, or or heal us once that mob has decided they hate us more than the tank. Thats fine. But once druids and shamans can replace us, well, I do have a problem with that. Druids and Shamen fill other ecological niches in the game. We don't have anywhere else to turn. Its healing or nothing for us.  And I don't care if the cost of rez rises to 1000 pp a pop, I will never rez someone in a group that turned me down for a druid and shaman tag team. Call it pettiness, but come on, Throw us a bone!<BR>
<BR>
Aberdeen Glamdringg<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

